        "title": "fix(plugin): harden schema and metadata fuzz boundaries",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Hardened malformed plugin/tool/schema metadata boundaries so hostile or unreadable synthetic plugin data is quarantined, omitted, diagnosed, or treated as absent instead of crashing provider routing, runtime tool resolution, Gateway/MCP catalogs, Codex prompt/report paths, plugin SDK helpers, and related assistant startup surfaces.\n- Kept fixtures synthetic: tests and notes use names like `fuzzplugin`, `mockplugin`, and `fuzz_move_*`, not the reported third-party plugin name.\n- Latest slice hardens bundled capability runtime capture: unreadable captured tool names now become a stable diagnostic, healthy sibling tools survive, and capability runtime records now carry manifest `contracts` so captured tools are checked against the right ownership contract.\n\n## Linked context\n\nWhich issue does this close?\n\nNo linked closing issue.\n\nWhich issues, PRs, or discussions are related?\n\nNo linked related issue.\n\nWas this requested by a maintainer or owner?\n\nMaintainer-directed hardening/debugging work.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: malformed runtime plugin tool schemas and hostile plugin/config/provider/manifest/native-approval/outbound-action metadata can crash, widen decisions, or bypass schema quarantine before normal OpenClaw diagnostics, setup, provider routing, gateway startup planning, Gateway catalog rendering, MCP loopback handling, approval forwarding, manifest/capability auth gating, provider payload conversion, prompt-cache setup, Codex reporting/instruction generation, plugin SDK normalization, agent-core tool lookup, cached plugin descriptor execution, static plugin tool registration, or bundled capability runtime capture completes.\n\nReal environment tested: local focused Vitest through `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs`, local focused lint/format checks, local autoreview, direct source probes from earlier slices, and earlier broad remote validation on direct AWS Crabbox Linux runners. Blacksmith Testbox was unavailable in this shell because `blacksmith auth login` is required.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n\n- Rebased onto `origin/main` `529ea02353d760e3636b76225fb507105933cca6`.\n- `CI=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/plugins/bundled-capability-runtime.test.ts --reporter=verbose`\n- `node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check src/plugins/bundled-capability-runtime.ts src/plugins/bundled-capability-runtime.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs src/plugins/bundled-capability-runtime.ts src/plugins/bundled-capability-runtime.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check -- src/plugins/bundled-capability-runtime.ts src/plugins/bundled-capability-runtime.test.ts`\n- private-name/private-path scrub over changed files and the working spec note\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local`\n- Earlier latest slices also passed focused Vitest, oxfmt, targeted oxlint, `git diff --check`, synthetic/private-name scrub, and clean local autoreview for static plugin tool registration, cached plugin descriptor execution, agent-core tool-name lookup, public plugin SDK tool normalization, embedded-agent allowlists, Google prompt-cache setup, Anthropic transport payloads, Google/Vertex tool config, OpenAI/Anthropic/Mistral provider conversion, OpenAI transport projection, Gateway MCP loopback, Codex report/instruction paths, prompt-cache observability, and related schema projection surfaces.\n- Earlier branch proofs include AWS Crabbox `pnpm check:changed` gates, including provider `aws`, lease `cbx_991a8c29acdf`, run `run_41811346ac17`, exit 0; and provider `aws`, lease `cbx_52b1fe398bd3`, run `run_c85914033aaa`, exit 0.\n\nEvidence after fix:\n\n- Latest branch head pushed: `221d8cd058b5d9149e545439eb36e8f78ad815bb`.\n- Latest local PR base/rebase point: `origin/main` `529ea02353d760e3636b76225fb507105933cca6`.\n- Bundled capability runtime records now copy manifest `contracts` from the loaded manifest record before captured tool contract enforcement.\n- Captured bundled tool names are read through a bounded accessor before filling `record.toolNames`, checking declared manifest ownership, or creating `registry.tools` entries.\n- Captured tools without a readable name now record `plugin tool registration missing readable tool name` and are skipped instead of failing the whole capability registry record.\n- Healthy captured siblings, such as synthetic `mockplugin_status`, remain registered and executable through the runtime registry entry.\n- Current branch diff, PR body, and private spec scrub pass for the reported plugin name and private paths.\n\nObserved result after fix:\n\n- A synthetic `fuzzplugin` bundled capability tool with an unreadable `name` getter no longer marks the whole capability plugin as failed.\n- A healthy synthetic `mockplugin_status` sibling survives the same capture pass and appears in the bundled capability runtime registry.\n- Manifest-owned captured tools are checked against copied manifest `contracts` instead of being treated as undeclared due to a fresh runtime record missing ownership metadata.\n- Existing focused slices continue to preserve healthy siblings while omitting only malformed descriptors across plugin runtime resolution, provider tools, central schema projection, Gateway/MCP, Codex reporting/instruction paths, prompt-cache diagnostics, and outbound action handling.\n\nWhat was not tested:\n\n- Blacksmith Testbox `pnpm check:changed` was not run because `blacksmith` is not authenticated in this shell.\n- The latest broad Crabbox gates predate the newest bundled capability capture, static registration, cached descriptor, agent-core, plugin SDK, embedded-agent, prompt-cache, transport, provider, Gateway MCP, and Codex report/instruction slices.\n- No live third-party plugin was referenced or exercised; tests intentionally use synthetic `fuzzplugin`/`mockplugin` fixtures.\n\n## Current review state\n\n- PR remains draft while this fuzzing/hardening lane continues.\n- Latest local autoreview after the bundled capability capture fix: clean, no accepted/actionable findings.\n- Latest pushed commit: `221d8cd058b5d9149e545439eb36e8f78ad815bb` (`fix(plugins): guard bundled capability tool capture`).\n",
